description.narrative: With UNICEF support new guidelines and educational opportunities for social workers within the child protection and educational systems were developed, the quality of alternative care was strengthened, the political will to tackle violence against children was mobilized, the testing of a new disability status determination system was successfully implemented, positive parenting services were created, and the access to and quality of general education services were enhanced. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/12/2019

title.narrative: # of Social Workers per 100,000 population (RAM and SMQ indicator)
MoLHSA is supported in piloting and implementation of the functional model of disability assessment and status determination

actual.value: 2019:In 2019 the piloting on the new system of diability assessment and status determination started in Adjara region of Georgia. It consists of testing assessment instrument as well as a new operational procedures related to status determination. The pilot will be completed in Spring 2020.

title.narrative: New framework and methodology for disability assessment and status determination developed

actual.value: 2019:The model of the new system of disability assessment and status determination has been developed and approaved by major stakeholders. Standardization of the new functional assessment instrument for CWD is underway.
